      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Hydroboration of 2-methyl-2-pentene at 25 °C, followed by oxidation with alkaline H<sub>2</sub>O<sub>2</sub>, yields 2-methyl-3-pentanol, but hydroboration at 160 °C followed by oxidation yields 4-methyl-1-pentanol. Suggest a mechanism.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBbndTIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--b9029f0163c40b74f36828c3e59f988b3028aac0/OChem_08_EC_031.jpg\" alt=\"A 2-pathway reaction shows the formation of 2-methyl-3-pentanol and 4-methyl-1-pentanol from 2-methyl-2-pentene at slightly different reaction temperaures.\">",
